1
00:00:29,446 --> 00:00:30,905
(SNORING)

2
00:01:03,146 --> 00:01:05,731
Hey, Bud! Get up!

3
00:01:11,238 --> 00:01:12,404
(ENGINE SPUTTERS)

4
00:01:19,412 --> 00:01:21,038
(BOTH SCREAMING)

5
00:01:43,019 --> 00:01:44,937
Pete, can't get through.

6
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:50,609
That's funny.
It seems pretty clear over here.

7
00:01:55,448 --> 00:01:56,699
(INDISTINCT SCREAMING)

8
00:01:57,117 --> 00:01:58,075
Tanker Base.

9
00:01:58,159 --> 00:02:01,036
Tanker Base,
this is Fire Boss. Over.

10
00:02:01,121 --> 00:02:02,162
WOMAN: Go ahead, Boss.

11
00:02:02,247 --> 00:02:03,747
FIRE BOSS: We've got
a situation here.

12
00:02:03,832 --> 00:02:06,876
Sector K, that's for,
"Kwick, we're kooking."

13
00:02:07,377 --> 00:02:10,087
WOMAN: Cavalry coming up
inside four minutes.

14
00:02:10,505 --> 00:02:13,632
Tanker 57 to Fire Boss.
Make that one minute.

15
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:17,511
Peter St. Peter,
don't do this to me. How much fuel you got left?

16
00:02:19,139 --> 00:02:21,056
I love it
in the kitchen, baby. You know that.

17
00:02:22,475 --> 00:02:26,645
Peter St. Peter,
you've got that Evel Knievel sound in your voice I hate.

18
00:02:27,022 --> 00:02:30,149
I want to blow
out this one tree, funny face...

19
00:02:30,525 --> 00:02:32,610
...and make a wish
for your birthday.

20
00:02:32,694 --> 00:02:34,862
You want to keep flying,
land that plane.

21
00:02:35,322 --> 00:02:36,655
Do what the lady says.

22
00:02:36,948 --> 00:02:40,242
(FAKING STATIC)
In the trees...

23
00:02:40,744 --> 00:02:42,119
Obscuring...

24
00:02:42,329 --> 00:02:44,330
Excuse me, I didn't
quite catch that.

25
00:02:56,676 --> 00:02:58,260
Take over, Frank.
Yeah.

26
00:03:12,108 --> 00:03:13,692
Tanker 57 to Tanker Base.

27
00:03:14,361 --> 00:03:16,654
I've got a small
inconvenience here.

28
00:03:17,405 --> 00:03:18,489
Talk to me, Pete.

29
00:03:19,282 --> 00:03:21,909
I may have
overestimated my fuel just a tad.

30
00:03:22,410 --> 00:03:26,538
I see the base and my
right engine is fine, so there shouldn't be any...

31
00:03:27,540 --> 00:03:28,582
...problem.

32
00:03:28,875 --> 00:03:29,917
What do you need?

33
00:03:31,670 --> 00:03:32,795
What do you need?

34
00:03:32,921 --> 00:03:34,046
Glider practice.

35
00:03:36,883 --> 00:03:38,384
(ALARM RINGING)

36
00:03:41,805 --> 00:03:42,805
FRANK: (OVER MEGAPHONE)
We've got a situation.

37
00:03:42,889 --> 00:03:44,431
Flier coming in, dead stick.

38
00:03:48,103 --> 00:03:50,813
This is good.
I was rusty on panic.

39
00:03:53,733 --> 00:03:55,484
No problem. I've got
the airport in sight.

40
00:03:57,195 --> 00:03:58,654
A nice little headwind.

41
00:04:04,452 --> 00:04:05,828
(WHISTLING)

42
00:04:12,335 --> 00:04:14,586
(PETE WHISTLING
OVER MEGAPHONE)

43
00:04:29,436 --> 00:04:30,978
(BLOWING RASPBERRY)

44
00:04:31,604 --> 00:04:33,147
(SIREN WAILING)

45
00:04:46,161 --> 00:04:47,578
Up and over.

46
00:04:48,621 --> 00:04:52,291
Come on, Mama.
Up and over. Up and over.

47
00:04:52,375 --> 00:04:53,417
(WHISPERING) Please, please.

48
00:04:53,752 --> 00:04:56,962
Come on, Mama,
we're too cute to die.

49
00:04:57,630 --> 00:05:00,174
(BIRTHDAY MUSIC PLAYING
ON MEGAPHONE)

50
00:05:14,773 --> 00:05:15,814
Up!

51
00:05:18,735 --> 00:05:20,486
There he is!

52
00:05:21,446 --> 00:05:22,654
Okay.

53
00:05:29,370 --> 00:05:30,996
(CROWD WHOOPING)

54
00:05:34,501 --> 00:05:35,793
(GASPING)

55
00:05:55,814 --> 00:05:57,064
(INDISTINCT)

56
00:06:04,280 --> 00:06:05,906
(PEOPLE CHEERING)

57
00:06:19,212 --> 00:06:21,004
Happy birthday.

58
00:06:33,351 --> 00:06:35,310
I'm taking a plane.
Why?

59
00:06:35,395 --> 00:06:36,520
This time
he's really done it.

60
00:06:36,604 --> 00:06:37,646
Done what?

61
00:06:41,401 --> 00:06:42,609
(BLOWS)

62
00:06:46,990 --> 00:06:48,490
Oh, Christ.

63
00:06:56,791 --> 00:06:59,501
Happy birthday to you...

64
00:07:00,170 --> 00:07:01,420
Take off!

65
00:07:01,921 --> 00:07:04,256
You don't even
understand how I feel!

66
00:07:04,340 --> 00:07:06,466
This time I'm
going to show him.

67
00:07:08,928 --> 00:07:10,387
Excuse me, Willy.

68
00:07:18,188 --> 00:07:20,439
You magnificent pagan god!

69
00:07:20,565 --> 00:07:21,648
PETE: Thanks, Al.

70
00:07:22,358 --> 00:07:23,650
What gives?

71
00:07:23,776 --> 00:07:25,110
She's showing you.

72
00:07:26,446 --> 00:07:27,487
She's a great girl.

73
00:07:32,952 --> 00:07:34,870
She's great.
Showing me what?

74
00:07:34,954 --> 00:07:36,496
I didn't know it
was her birthday.

75
00:07:36,623 --> 00:07:38,874
It's because you don't
love her like I do.

76
00:07:42,629 --> 00:07:44,504
Where did you get
that oil on your face? Where?

77
00:07:44,589 --> 00:07:47,132
It's here. Look.
It's terrible.

78
00:07:48,134 --> 00:07:49,384
Thanks.

79
00:07:49,719 --> 00:07:51,637
What do you mean,
"showing me"?

80
00:08:00,021 --> 00:08:01,730
I don't like her
flying that. Now you're getting it.

81
00:08:25,964 --> 00:08:27,297
(BOTH SCREAMING)

82
00:08:36,057 --> 00:08:37,307
You're mad at me.
I can tell.

83
00:08:37,392 --> 00:08:38,892
It's okay. I'm just moody.

84
00:08:40,270 --> 00:08:41,687
Beautiful day.

85
00:08:43,064 --> 00:08:45,399
Yes, it is.
How was my landing?

86
00:08:45,817 --> 00:08:46,817
Nearly perfect.

87
00:08:46,901 --> 00:08:47,943
Wow! Thanks.

88
00:08:49,404 --> 00:08:50,779
You only fly like that
when I'm watching.

89
00:08:50,863 --> 00:08:53,115
I always come in
on three wheels.

90
00:08:53,199 --> 00:08:56,493
Perverse, aren't you?
Don't do that, Dorinda.

91
00:08:56,828 --> 00:08:58,036
(BLOWING)

92
00:08:58,121 --> 00:09:00,831
Can she take
the Wiley scrapper? The Wiley vet?

93
00:09:01,291 --> 00:09:04,334
Who knows?
There's a quick left. Look out.

94
00:09:04,669 --> 00:09:06,920
Level off
when you come in.

95
00:09:07,005 --> 00:09:08,088
Don't tell me what to do.

96
00:09:08,172 --> 00:09:09,172
What did I say?

97
00:09:09,257 --> 00:09:10,465
You got something
in your teeth.

98
00:09:10,550 --> 00:09:13,427
(CHUCKLES) I ain't
falling for that.

99
00:09:13,678 --> 00:09:14,886
You caught some
heat coming in.

100
00:09:14,971 --> 00:09:16,138
You know women.

101
00:09:16,222 --> 00:09:17,681
(SCOFFS)
I mean your plane.

102
00:09:19,017 --> 00:09:21,268
I might have to kill
you for that remark.

103
00:09:21,352 --> 00:09:23,478
Every time you come in,
the fire trucks come out.

104
00:09:24,689 --> 00:09:26,982
Nails, go play golf.
It's my plane.

105
00:09:27,066 --> 00:09:29,776
You've got something
between your teeth.

106
00:09:30,236 --> 00:09:31,528
What makes you think
I forgot your birthday?

107
00:09:31,612 --> 00:09:32,738
Why do you do this?

108
00:09:47,837 --> 00:09:50,088
Want to dance?
There's a dance tonight.

109
00:09:50,673 --> 00:09:51,923
Coming through.

110
00:09:54,427 --> 00:09:55,677
(BLOWING)

111
00:09:58,264 --> 00:09:58,305
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

112
00:09:58,306 --> 00:10:00,057
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

113
00:10:20,161 --> 00:10:21,787
Please, take mine.

114
00:10:25,124 --> 00:10:26,750
(CLEARS THROAT)

115
00:10:34,133 --> 00:10:35,634
This is for you.

116
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:37,469
You're incredible.

117
00:10:37,929 --> 00:10:39,429
You think you
can buy me off

118
00:10:39,514 --> 00:10:42,808
with some crummy present
you got in an airport gift shop.

119
00:10:43,267 --> 00:10:44,684
It's worked before.

120
00:10:51,442 --> 00:10:52,692
I don't want it.

121
00:10:53,945 --> 00:10:54,986
Take it.

122
00:10:55,321 --> 00:10:56,321
Fathead.

123
00:10:56,948 --> 00:10:58,698
"Fathead"?
Yeah.

124
00:10:59,033 --> 00:11:00,450
I don't want it.
Yes, you do.

125
00:11:00,576 --> 00:11:01,993
I don't.
You do.

126
00:11:02,203 --> 00:11:03,495
You do. You really do.

127
00:11:03,663 --> 00:11:04,913
You really don't?
No.

128
00:11:13,631 --> 00:11:14,840
(GASPS)

129
00:11:20,012 --> 00:11:21,471
Oh, Pete.

130
00:11:28,521 --> 00:11:30,147
Girl clothes!

131
00:11:30,565 --> 00:11:32,315
Get back!
Don't touch that!

132
00:11:37,071 --> 00:11:40,157
Why didn't you tell me
before I lost my temper?

133
00:11:41,033 --> 00:11:42,951
So you do like dresses.

134
00:11:44,245 --> 00:11:47,789
It's not the dress.
It's the way you see me.

135
00:12:04,891 --> 00:12:06,349
Know what this
place reminds me of?

136
00:12:06,434 --> 00:12:08,727
I'll bet you a beer
you're going to tell me.

137
00:12:10,688 --> 00:12:11,897
You lose.

138
00:12:16,986 --> 00:12:19,404
Love! It ain't
what it used to be.

139
00:12:20,656 --> 00:12:22,240
There have only
ever been two kinds.

140
00:12:23,409 --> 00:12:25,577
Flash fires,
which are all flame,

141
00:12:25,661 --> 00:12:27,829
burn themselves out
and leave nothing.

142
00:12:29,373 --> 00:12:32,792
Then there is
the long burning. That is nature's burn.

143
00:12:33,294 --> 00:12:35,378
Even when you
think it's out...

144
00:12:35,671 --> 00:12:37,672
...the forest floor
is warm to the touch.

145
00:12:38,674 --> 00:12:40,675
That's what you
and Dorinda have got.

146
00:12:42,261 --> 00:12:43,929
You're a poet, Al.

147
00:12:44,764 --> 00:12:47,682
You're a really bad poet,
but you're a poet.

148
00:13:00,238 --> 00:13:03,740
To hell with it.
This place reminds me of World War II.

149
00:13:04,450 --> 00:13:05,408
This is deep.

150
00:13:05,493 --> 00:13:07,619
I wasn't in it,
but think about it.

151
00:13:07,787 --> 00:13:09,955
The beer is warm,
the hall is a Quonset...

152
00:13:10,289 --> 00:13:15,168
...there are B-26s outside,
hotshot pilots inside. Airstrip in the woods.

153
00:13:15,628 --> 00:13:18,213
It's England!
Everything but Glenn Miller.

154
00:13:19,298 --> 00:13:22,676
Except we bomb places
that are already burning.

155
00:13:23,427 --> 00:13:24,678
You see, Pete,

156
00:13:25,805 --> 00:13:27,430
there ain't no war here.

157
00:13:27,723 --> 00:13:28,807
What's taking her so long?

158
00:13:29,016 --> 00:13:31,309
That's why they don't
make movies called,

159
00:13:31,394 --> 00:13:33,603
Night Raid to Boise,
Idaho or...

160
00:13:34,063 --> 00:13:36,189
...Firemen Strike at Dawn.

161
00:13:36,816 --> 00:13:39,067
And this is why you're
not exactly a hero

162
00:13:39,151 --> 00:13:41,361
for taking
the chances you take.

163
00:13:42,446 --> 00:13:44,906
You're more of
what I would call a dickhead.

164
00:13:45,992 --> 00:13:47,826
Is this heading somewhere?

165
00:13:49,078 --> 00:13:51,955
Here's my point.
I'm talking to this guy.

166
00:13:52,456 --> 00:13:56,459
He tells me about
this tanker school in Flat Rock, Colorado.

167
00:13:56,669 --> 00:13:58,044
A school for fire pilots.

168
00:13:58,129 --> 00:14:00,213
There are no forest fires
in Flat Rock, Colorado,

169
00:14:00,298 --> 00:14:02,299
because there are no trees.

170
00:14:03,175 --> 00:14:05,927
That is why they
call it Flat Rock, you dunce.

171
00:14:13,102 --> 00:14:14,936
I think they
know this, Pete.

172
00:14:16,022 --> 00:14:17,939
That's why they
chose Flat Rock.

173
00:14:18,107 --> 00:14:20,025
So they could start
a few little fires

174
00:14:20,109 --> 00:14:21,985
without burning
down all of Colorado.

175
00:14:23,195 --> 00:14:24,487
The idea...

176
00:14:25,031 --> 00:14:26,948
...is to teach
guys to do drops

177
00:14:27,033 --> 00:14:28,617
and set up test areas
to teach pilots

178
00:14:28,701 --> 00:14:30,243
who want to get their
Initial Attack cards.

179
00:14:30,369 --> 00:14:31,369
Are you following this?

180
00:14:32,204 --> 00:14:33,246
Yeah. Yeah.

181
00:14:33,539 --> 00:14:37,208
They're looking for
a great teacher,

182
00:14:37,668 --> 00:14:39,336
like a commanding officer.

183
00:14:39,837 --> 00:14:43,006
An experienced guy
who might be looking for a change of pace.

184
00:14:43,257 --> 00:14:46,176
Year-round employment,
great paycheck. Are you with me?

185
00:14:47,511 --> 00:14:50,347
I'm way ahead of you.
It's not a bad notion.

186
00:14:52,933 --> 00:14:54,643
I'm glad you
see it like this.

187
00:14:54,727 --> 00:14:56,686
It's a terrific idea.

188
00:14:57,521 --> 00:14:58,730
You'd be perfect for it.

189
00:14:59,357 --> 00:15:01,483
Me? I'm not
talking about me.

190
00:15:01,734 --> 00:15:04,069
I don't need a day job.
I'm very happy...

191
00:15:30,429 --> 00:15:31,638
Gosh.

192
00:15:48,531 --> 00:15:50,031
(CROWD CHEERS)

193
00:16:00,459 --> 00:16:01,835
Beer, please.

194
00:16:02,169 --> 00:16:03,962
In a champagne glass.

195
00:16:04,505 --> 00:16:05,630
Make it two.

196
00:16:05,715 --> 00:16:06,840
Let me make
something clear.

197
00:16:07,508 --> 00:16:09,217
If you think
you can make me

198
00:16:09,301 --> 00:16:11,970
weak in the knees by
giving me girl clothes,

199
00:16:12,054 --> 00:16:15,140
you're as out-of-date
as your airplane. You know?

200
00:16:15,307 --> 00:16:16,266
I know.

201
00:16:16,350 --> 00:16:19,477
I'm not weak in the knees.
I'm weak in the head.

202
00:16:19,687 --> 00:16:21,312
You're beautiful.
I love you.

203
00:16:21,981 --> 00:16:23,148
I know.

204
00:16:23,941 --> 00:16:25,358
So tell me you love me.

205
00:16:26,318 --> 00:16:27,777
Please, please.

206
00:16:28,404 --> 00:16:30,029
Tell me, tell me.

207
00:16:30,489 --> 00:16:32,073
Tell me, tell me!

208
00:16:32,158 --> 00:16:34,951
In front of all
these people?

209
00:16:35,202 --> 00:16:36,286
You mean Carl?

210
00:16:36,954 --> 00:16:38,413
Le Budweiser.

211
00:16:38,497 --> 00:16:40,039
(IN MOCK FRENCH ACCENT)
The '89.

212
00:16:40,499 --> 00:16:42,250
BOTH: Thanks, Carl.

213
00:16:47,047 --> 00:16:48,256
To us.

214
00:16:49,341 --> 00:16:50,759
Always.

215
00:16:55,014 --> 00:16:57,891
(EXHALES) Hmm.
St. Louis. Southside.

216
00:16:58,350 --> 00:16:59,517
(LAUGHS)

217
00:17:02,688 --> 00:17:04,105
You never laugh
at my jokes.

218
00:17:04,190 --> 00:17:05,607
What jokes?

219
00:17:08,235 --> 00:17:09,986
Left rudder. Left.
I know, I know.

220
00:17:27,963 --> 00:17:29,422
It's too bad we
don't have a song.

221
00:17:29,507 --> 00:17:30,882
(GASPS)

222
00:17:30,966 --> 00:17:34,427
You know, when couples
say, "Honey, they're playing our song."

223
00:17:34,512 --> 00:17:36,304
I can't believe you forgot.

224
00:17:36,388 --> 00:17:37,680
What, we have a song?

225
00:17:37,765 --> 00:17:38,973
Yes, we have a song.

226
00:17:39,058 --> 00:17:40,975
You big lug!
You'll break my heart.

227
00:17:41,060 --> 00:17:42,685
You're calling me
a "big lug"?

228
00:17:42,770 --> 00:17:45,980
Let's try that signaling
to the band bit.

229
00:17:46,065 --> 00:17:47,982
It works in the movies.

230
00:17:48,317 --> 00:17:49,776
Guys, hit it.

231
00:17:50,069 --> 00:17:51,903
(SOFT MUSIC PLAYING)

232
00:17:58,118 --> 00:17:59,410
They

233
00:18:00,412 --> 00:18:03,581
Asked me how I knew

234
00:18:04,750 --> 00:18:07,627
My true love was true

235
00:18:13,592 --> 00:18:16,177
I of course replied

236
00:18:18,013 --> 00:18:20,807
Something here inside

237
00:18:22,393 --> 00:18:26,062
Cannot be denied

238
00:18:29,567 --> 00:18:30,984
(BOTH LAUGHING)

239
00:18:32,194 --> 00:18:33,736
You laugh like a donkey.

240
00:18:33,821 --> 00:18:34,988
I do not.

241
00:18:35,072 --> 00:18:36,155
Do, too.
(MIMICKING DONKEY SNORTING)

242
00:18:36,240 --> 00:18:38,783
I don't do that.

243
00:18:53,465 --> 00:18:55,383
Do you know him?
Never saw him before.

244
00:18:55,467 --> 00:18:57,844
You smiled at
a poor defenseless guy.

245
00:18:57,970 --> 00:18:59,512
Yes, I think I did.

246
00:18:59,597 --> 00:19:01,055
That was
a damn-fool thing to do.

247
00:19:01,140 --> 00:19:02,432
Why, darling?

248
00:19:02,600 --> 00:19:04,642
You are giving
smiles away now?

249
00:19:04,727 --> 00:19:06,060
I'm feeling very fine.

250
00:19:06,145 --> 00:19:08,563
Are you sure you're
not feeling feverish?

251
00:19:08,647 --> 00:19:11,482
I'm all right as long
as we keep dancing.

252
00:19:13,819 --> 00:19:15,403
Happy birthday.

253
00:19:15,487 --> 00:19:16,654
It's not my birthday.

254
00:19:16,739 --> 00:19:17,822
It isn't?
No.

255
00:19:18,240 --> 00:19:19,991
I forgot your
birthday again?

256
00:19:20,117 --> 00:19:21,826
No, you just
remembered it wrong.

257
00:19:38,177 --> 00:19:39,802
My turn, flyboy.

258
00:19:45,017 --> 00:19:46,309
Hi, Donnie. (CHUCKLES)

259
00:19:46,435 --> 00:19:47,685
You look like an angel.

260
00:19:48,228 --> 00:19:50,939
Let's go start
ourselves a little fire.

261
00:19:51,690 --> 00:19:53,524
Airborne, cutting in.

262
00:19:53,734 --> 00:19:54,776
Stand in the door.

263
00:19:54,860 --> 00:19:56,736
Whoa! Time out now.

264
00:19:57,363 --> 00:20:01,074
Nobody dances with this dress
until they wash their hands.

265
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:03,159
(INDISTINCT MURMURING)

266
00:20:11,502 --> 00:20:12,794
Miss Scarlett?

267
00:20:18,217 --> 00:20:19,550
Oh, boys.

268
00:20:20,469 --> 00:20:23,179
You want to dance
with my girl, you've got to wipe your hands.

269
00:20:23,430 --> 00:20:26,224
That's it. Whoa!
That's not a towel.

270
00:20:32,064 --> 00:20:33,982
(SINGING INCOHERENTLY)

271
00:20:46,829 --> 00:20:50,081
That's good. Very good.
You missed a spot.

272
00:21:08,934 --> 00:21:10,059
(BONES CREAKING)

273
00:21:10,144 --> 00:21:11,436
Oh, God!

274
00:22:13,165 --> 00:22:14,665
Is that your plane?

275
00:22:15,834 --> 00:22:17,502
Yes, that is mine.

276
00:22:18,504 --> 00:22:20,505
Come on. A shortcut.

277
00:23:03,173 --> 00:23:04,632
Pete?
Hmm?

278
00:23:05,050 --> 00:23:06,259
Haircut.

279
00:23:06,343 --> 00:23:07,385
What?

280
00:23:08,720 --> 00:23:10,888
You want me to get
a haircut today?

281
00:23:11,640 --> 00:23:13,141
Cat food.

282
00:23:13,392 --> 00:23:14,809
Green apples.

283
00:23:15,185 --> 00:23:17,311
You're shopping in
your sleep again.

284
00:23:17,396 --> 00:23:19,480
Chicken wings.
Tempura batter.

285
00:23:19,606 --> 00:23:20,773
What is for dinner?

286
00:23:20,858 --> 00:23:22,483
Toilet paper. Soap.

287
00:23:22,776 --> 00:23:24,694
And dessert?
Kitty litter.

288
00:23:25,404 --> 00:23:26,654
Q-tips.

289
00:23:27,072 --> 00:23:28,531
Socks.

290
00:23:40,377 --> 00:23:41,627
(WHISPERS) Pete?

291
00:23:43,755 --> 00:23:44,797
What?

292
00:23:45,257 --> 00:23:47,049
You have a bad dream?

293
00:24:00,772 --> 00:24:02,231
It's cold.

294
00:24:07,738 --> 00:24:08,779
Come on.

295
00:24:11,283 --> 00:24:12,783
I'm watching the fire.

296
00:24:14,119 --> 00:24:16,245
We don't do fires
at night.

297
00:24:16,705 --> 00:24:17,955
We do fires in the day.

298
00:24:18,207 --> 00:24:21,918
At night, we eat, drink
and be mad for each other.

299
00:24:23,879 --> 00:24:25,254
Mmm. Sounds like
an all right life.

300
00:24:25,339 --> 00:24:26,422
I like it.

301
00:24:26,798 --> 00:24:28,007
I thought I might try it.

302
00:24:28,091 --> 00:24:29,217
Try what?

303
00:24:29,843 --> 00:24:31,177
Tankers.

304
00:24:34,056 --> 00:24:36,807
I'd like to get
type-rated for air tankers.

305
00:24:37,768 --> 00:24:40,478
Then we'd both be up
there instead of

306
00:24:40,562 --> 00:24:41,854
one of us on the ground
and the other...

307
00:24:42,648 --> 00:24:43,814
Forget it.

308
00:24:43,982 --> 00:24:45,608
I could make it in a year.

309
00:24:46,443 --> 00:24:49,779
With three years
of hauling freight, I've done 1,000 hours.

310
00:24:50,405 --> 00:24:53,282
I saw the last
four minutes. Forget it.

311
00:24:56,286 --> 00:24:57,662
It's none of your beeswax.

312
00:24:58,372 --> 00:25:01,082
It is my beeswax and
I won't let you do it.

313
00:25:02,334 --> 00:25:03,668
How will you stop me?

314
00:25:03,835 --> 00:25:05,169
By telling you "no."

315
00:25:06,338 --> 00:25:09,757
By asking you nicely.

316
00:25:11,426 --> 00:25:13,511
Dorinda, honey, please.

317
00:25:14,346 --> 00:25:16,264
Don't be
a pigheaded fool.

318
00:25:18,767 --> 00:25:20,601
That is irresistible.

319
00:25:31,113 --> 00:25:33,531
Now you listen to
me for a change.

320
00:25:34,574 --> 00:25:36,784
(SIGHS)
I'll make you a deal.

321
00:25:37,286 --> 00:25:39,787
Here's your chance to
get me out of the air.

322
00:25:39,997 --> 00:25:44,500
I'll ground myself
in Flat Rock and be your girl.

323
00:25:44,584 --> 00:25:45,793
Have you been
talking to Al?

324
00:25:45,877 --> 00:25:47,044
Or...

325
00:25:50,882 --> 00:25:53,968
...I head off on my own
and tonight is goodbye.

326
00:25:55,220 --> 00:25:58,723
I'll find my own piece of sky
and a guy who flies sensible.

327
00:25:59,182 --> 00:26:00,599
I fly sensible.

328
00:26:02,060 --> 00:26:04,061
Not when something
is on fire.

329
00:26:04,730 --> 00:26:06,147
That is the deal.

330
00:26:10,068 --> 00:26:11,444
Then it is no deal.

331
00:26:13,905 --> 00:26:15,156
(SIGHS)

332
00:26:15,407 --> 00:26:17,033
Let's change the subject.

333
00:26:17,200 --> 00:26:18,576
What's going on?

334
00:26:19,328 --> 00:26:21,162
Why are you doing this?
Because...

335
00:26:21,246 --> 00:26:23,247
Because why? Why?
Because...

336
00:26:24,750 --> 00:26:26,042
Why are you doing this?

337
00:26:26,168 --> 00:26:27,501
Because I love you.

338
00:26:27,586 --> 00:26:31,380
Fighting fires is what
I do and it is what I love, and you know that!

339
00:26:31,965 --> 00:26:35,259
What the hell is going on
that you want me to quit?

340
00:26:35,802 --> 00:26:38,471
You want me to move
to Colorado and

341
00:26:38,555 --> 00:26:42,475
teach pretend fires
to trainees like I'm going to an office?

342
00:26:42,559 --> 00:26:43,601
Pete.

343
00:26:48,148 --> 00:26:49,607
Your number is up.

344
00:26:50,192 --> 00:26:52,109
When my number is up...

345
00:26:53,779 --> 00:26:55,196
...it is up.

346
00:26:56,782 --> 00:26:57,907
Right?

347
00:27:00,410 --> 00:27:04,580
I could just as soon
buy it ferrying Bibles to Salt Lake City.

348
00:27:05,457 --> 00:27:07,833
When it is your turn,
I don't want to be around.

349
00:27:07,918 --> 00:27:10,127
I think that is
very selfish of you.

350
00:27:11,129 --> 00:27:13,547
You should be
at the funeral,

351
00:27:13,632 --> 00:27:16,509
crying and looking
terrific before you enter the nunnery.

352
00:27:16,593 --> 00:27:18,386
You wish!

353
00:27:18,845 --> 00:27:22,139
I'll have better things
to do and better men to do them with.

354
00:27:26,645 --> 00:27:29,271
Forget about these
other men, Dorinda.

355
00:27:29,815 --> 00:27:31,232
You'll never be
with another man.

356
00:27:31,566 --> 00:27:33,192
I will, too,
and he'll be tall.

357
00:27:33,276 --> 00:27:34,568
No, Dorinda.

358
00:27:34,653 --> 00:27:35,945
Why not?

359
00:27:36,571 --> 00:27:38,239
You'll never get over me.

360
00:27:38,323 --> 00:27:39,949
Don't kid yourself.

361
00:27:40,033 --> 00:27:42,326
No one will ever
be as much fun.

362
00:27:42,411 --> 00:27:43,577
Fun?

363
00:27:44,913 --> 00:27:47,415
You think I have fun
when you have fun?

364
00:27:49,960 --> 00:27:51,961
When you fly into
some narrow canyon,

365
00:27:52,045 --> 00:27:55,506
you think I'm
on the ground going, "Boy, this is fun"?

366
00:28:03,265 --> 00:28:05,516
I could understand
how you fly

367
00:28:05,767 --> 00:28:08,978
if you were
risking yourself for civilization.

368
00:28:09,729 --> 00:28:11,188
If you were...

369
00:28:12,858 --> 00:28:15,693
...putting your life on
the line for another life,

370
00:28:16,319 --> 00:28:17,903
anybody's life.

371
00:28:21,616 --> 00:28:23,200
I love you, Pete.

372
00:28:24,202 --> 00:28:26,036
But I'm not enjoying it.

373
00:28:31,126 --> 00:28:34,462
(SNIFFLES) Every time
you take off,

374
00:28:34,546 --> 00:28:37,465
I wait for
the phone to ring.

375
00:28:38,717 --> 00:28:41,886
I go to bed sick
and I get up scared.

376
00:28:42,012 --> 00:28:46,515
I don't like being
sick inside all the time.

377
00:28:47,058 --> 00:28:49,935
Do think I like being afraid
that you won't come back?

378
00:28:50,061 --> 00:28:51,729
Okay. Okay.

379
00:28:53,523 --> 00:28:54,815
Look... (SIGHS)

380
00:28:58,278 --> 00:29:01,572
...I have an idea.
Bear with me a second.

381
00:29:01,656 --> 00:29:02,656
Okay.

382
00:29:02,741 --> 00:29:06,285
Keep an open mind,
because it is a pretty radical idea.

383
00:29:13,293 --> 00:29:17,838
Al told me about
a training school in Flat Rock, Colorado.

384
00:29:20,967 --> 00:29:24,261
They need
a commanding officer and I was wondering,

385
00:29:24,387 --> 00:29:26,722
why don't I take you
to Colorado and you could be my girl

386
00:29:26,806 --> 00:29:30,184
and I could teach those
geeks to fight fires.

387
00:29:31,603 --> 00:29:34,021
You know, till they could
put out a cigar at 200 feet

388
00:29:34,105 --> 00:29:36,190
and I'd come
home every night

389
00:29:37,359 --> 00:29:40,361
and we'd have an apartment
with a microwave oven.

390
00:29:42,280 --> 00:29:43,781
(PHONE RINGS)

391
00:29:44,199 --> 00:29:45,824
Don't answer it.

392
00:29:46,243 --> 00:29:47,451
I won't.

393
00:29:48,411 --> 00:29:50,162
It's not my phone.

394
00:30:00,757 --> 00:30:02,174
Hi, Al.

395
00:30:02,509 --> 00:30:03,551
No.

396
00:30:03,635 --> 00:30:06,053
No, because
it is my day off.

397
00:30:06,846 --> 00:30:09,932
Get yourself another pilot.
I'm hanging up my spurs.

398
00:30:10,433 --> 00:30:12,393
That's right. (CHUCKLES)

399
00:30:13,186 --> 00:30:15,479
Yes, she's a great
girl, isn't she?

400
00:30:20,652 --> 00:30:21,986
Okay.

401
00:30:25,323 --> 00:30:26,865
Al is on his way over.

402
00:30:27,909 --> 00:30:29,660
It's your lay-off day.

403
00:30:30,495 --> 00:30:32,705
There is a new burn
in the south rim.

404
00:30:34,833 --> 00:30:37,501
There are already two
pilots down. (SIGHS)

405
00:30:38,336 --> 00:30:39,378
Down?

406
00:30:40,505 --> 00:30:41,797
Sick.

407
00:30:44,551 --> 00:30:46,343
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

408
00:30:57,480 --> 00:30:58,606
What you got?

409
00:30:58,690 --> 00:31:02,276
We've got nine hot spots.
We're only taking care of three of them.

410
00:31:09,451 --> 00:31:10,701
(GRUNTS)

411
00:31:46,446 --> 00:31:48,113
(TIRES SCREECHING)

412
00:32:05,715 --> 00:32:07,174
I love you!

413
00:32:09,094 --> 00:32:11,387
You can't leave
without knowing that.

414
00:32:11,471 --> 00:32:13,722
I know you do
and you know I do.

415
00:32:13,807 --> 00:32:17,768
How would I know that?
You never say the words!

416
00:32:17,852 --> 00:32:22,606
These days we've had,
last night. These things are fragile!

417
00:32:22,691 --> 00:32:25,943
What? We got
a lot of things settled last night.

418
00:32:26,027 --> 00:32:27,319
Shut up!

419
00:32:27,821 --> 00:32:29,780
Kiss me and fly!

420
00:33:02,313 --> 00:33:04,356
Dorinda, I love you!

421
00:33:05,358 --> 00:33:06,358
I love...

422
00:33:10,155 --> 00:33:12,030
I love you! (CHUCKLES)

423
00:33:26,755 --> 00:33:29,089
Al the Pal, this is Pete
St. Pete. Over.

424
00:33:30,175 --> 00:33:33,135
This is Al the Pal.
I've got you loud and proud.

425
00:33:34,053 --> 00:33:35,846
This is Fire Boss, over.

426
00:33:36,055 --> 00:33:37,347
AL: This is Al the Pal.

427
00:33:37,724 --> 00:33:40,934
Roger, Al.
Go for the leading edge of the fire.

428
00:33:41,770 --> 00:33:43,520
You got it.

429
00:33:44,522 --> 00:33:46,482
PETE: Two minutes
behind him, Boss.

430
00:33:47,859 --> 00:33:49,526
Good enough, good buddy.

431
00:33:59,579 --> 00:34:01,205
Get down!

432
00:34:04,459 --> 00:34:06,376
Save some fire for me.

433
00:34:07,212 --> 00:34:09,296
There is plenty of
fire for everybody.

434
00:34:09,380 --> 00:34:11,423
Watch his next pass
and build on that.

435
00:34:18,431 --> 00:34:20,224
Oh! Bad strike!

436
00:34:23,186 --> 00:34:24,520
Al, pull up.

437
00:34:25,772 --> 00:34:28,732
Goddamn it, I thought
that was it, man!

438
00:34:31,319 --> 00:34:32,611
Oh, shit.

439
00:34:43,039 --> 00:34:45,415
Al! What happened?

440
00:34:49,128 --> 00:34:50,170
PETE: Talk to me.
(ALARM BLARING)

441
00:34:50,255 --> 00:34:53,257
My engine is on fire!
Can you believe that?

442
00:34:53,925 --> 00:34:55,843
And I was in
such a good mood.

443
00:34:57,512 --> 00:34:58,804
(BEEPING)

444
00:35:03,309 --> 00:35:05,644
You think you
can make it back?

445
00:35:06,104 --> 00:35:07,688
It ain't happening!

446
00:35:07,772 --> 00:35:10,732
The fire will hit
the fuel tank any second! Damn!

447
00:35:10,984 --> 00:35:12,276
Use your extinguisher.

448
00:35:12,360 --> 00:35:13,527
Already did.

449
00:35:15,989 --> 00:35:17,531
I'm screwed.

450
00:35:30,628 --> 00:35:33,964
Pete, lighten up
or you won't pull out of that dive!

451
00:35:34,716 --> 00:35:36,842
Pete, this ain't
a dogfight, man!

452
00:35:39,095 --> 00:35:42,264
BOSS: Pete, this is the boss!
That dive is way too steep!

453
00:35:42,724 --> 00:35:44,266
Pull out of there!

454
00:35:44,350 --> 00:35:47,394
You're too heavy!
Get out of there!

455
00:35:49,022 --> 00:35:50,063
Now!

456
00:35:59,824 --> 00:36:02,075
Baby, you're the greatest!

457
00:36:06,497 --> 00:36:07,831
Come on.

458
00:36:24,724 --> 00:36:26,016
Get up!

459
00:36:30,104 --> 00:36:31,647
Come on, Pete, pull up.

460
00:36:42,116 --> 00:36:43,659
Come on, man.

461
00:36:44,035 --> 00:36:45,243
Get up!

462
00:36:53,962 --> 00:36:55,712
Oh, yes! He made it!

463
00:37:00,009 --> 00:37:01,343
(PANTING)

464
00:37:07,475 --> 00:37:10,185
That lucky son of a bitch.

465
00:37:15,733 --> 00:37:17,150
(LAUGHING)

466
00:38:36,564 --> 00:38:37,022
(MAN WHISTLING)

467
00:38:37,023 --> 00:38:38,148
(MAN WHISTLING)

468
00:39:31,452 --> 00:39:33,036
Hello, Pete.

469
00:39:34,747 --> 00:39:35,872
Hello.

470
00:39:37,542 --> 00:39:39,292
Hap.
Hello, Hap.

471
00:39:41,045 --> 00:39:43,130
That was quite
a show back there.

472
00:39:44,340 --> 00:39:45,590
Yes, ma'am.

473
00:39:47,885 --> 00:39:49,219
Take a seat.

474
00:39:49,345 --> 00:39:51,221
Okay. Thanks.

475
00:39:59,772 --> 00:40:02,858
I sure saved Al's bacon,
all right. (LAUGHING)

476
00:40:04,026 --> 00:40:08,196
Too bad about my port engine.
My fuel tank went up like...

477
00:40:13,786 --> 00:40:14,995
Just a minute.

478
00:40:15,121 --> 00:40:16,371
Comfy around the neck?

479
00:40:16,581 --> 00:40:18,248
Yeah. Yeah, it's fine.

480
00:40:18,833 --> 00:40:21,418
Listen, how did I
get out of that one?

481
00:40:21,627 --> 00:40:23,086
You didn't.

482
00:40:23,212 --> 00:40:24,421
I didn't?
Mmm-mmm.

483
00:40:25,798 --> 00:40:28,049
My plane blew up.
I remember that.

484
00:40:28,801 --> 00:40:30,427
A real fireball.

485
00:40:33,055 --> 00:40:36,266
Now I'm sitting
in the woods, getting my hair cut.

486
00:40:37,977 --> 00:40:40,520
Either I'm dead
or I'm crazy.

487
00:40:41,063 --> 00:40:42,814
You're not crazy, Pete.

488
00:40:48,613 --> 00:40:49,779
Hap.

489
00:40:52,158 --> 00:40:53,450
Don't think

490
00:40:53,534 --> 00:40:55,702
I'm doubting
your good faith.

491
00:40:55,953 --> 00:40:58,121
I just want to get
something clear.

492
00:40:59,624 --> 00:41:00,999
Okay?
Okay.

493
00:41:02,501 --> 00:41:03,501
Okay.

494
00:41:06,589 --> 00:41:07,714
I'm dead?

495
00:41:08,466 --> 00:41:09,966
That's right.

496
00:41:13,262 --> 00:41:14,471
I'm dead?

497
00:41:14,597 --> 00:41:15,722
Right.

498
00:41:17,350 --> 00:41:18,975
Keep the sideburns.

499
00:41:21,771 --> 00:41:24,147
(SIGHS) What a jerk
I turned out to be.

500
00:41:26,984 --> 00:41:28,485
Dead. (SCOFFS)

501
00:41:30,488 --> 00:41:32,197
What do you think of that?

502
00:41:37,620 --> 00:41:38,703
Dorinda.

503
00:41:40,164 --> 00:41:41,831
She's still not over it.

504
00:41:43,834 --> 00:41:48,505
I hope not. I've only
been dead 20 minutes.

505
00:41:49,173 --> 00:41:52,342
Yes and no.
Down there they think it's six months.

506
00:41:53,302 --> 00:41:55,387
Time is funny stuff.

507
00:41:55,763 --> 00:41:58,265
A lot funnier than
Einstein ever figured out.

508
00:41:58,349 --> 00:41:59,432
Yeah?

509
00:41:59,850 --> 00:42:01,226
How did he take it?

510
00:42:01,394 --> 00:42:03,353
That'll do it.

511
00:42:05,439 --> 00:42:06,690
Where was I?

512
00:42:07,650 --> 00:42:09,609
"Time is funny stuff."
Yes. That was it.

513
00:42:09,694 --> 00:42:13,113
Space has its points, too.
So in the five months since you crashed...

514
00:42:13,197 --> 00:42:14,614
You said it was
six months.

515
00:42:14,699 --> 00:42:18,118
That was then.
I'm explaining this to you in the wrong order.

516
00:42:19,412 --> 00:42:20,662
Hey, look!

517
00:42:24,750 --> 00:42:26,584
PETE: I did my first
solo in one of those!

518
00:42:26,711 --> 00:42:27,877
HAP: That's right.

519
00:42:28,546 --> 00:42:30,630
I did that!
That's right.

520
00:42:30,715 --> 00:42:35,093
Boy, was I nervous!
But you want to know a funny thing?

521
00:42:35,553 --> 00:42:39,055
Once I got up there,
I felt like a veteran.

522
00:42:39,473 --> 00:42:41,725
I couldn't do
anything wrong.

523
00:42:42,059 --> 00:42:45,562
I flew that plane
like Fats Waller flies his piano.

524
00:42:45,980 --> 00:42:47,981
I circled the field,
then I found

525
00:42:48,065 --> 00:42:50,150
a perfect sideslip
in the wind

526
00:42:50,234 --> 00:42:52,652
and I came in
just like a leaf.

527
00:42:53,195 --> 00:42:54,446
That's right.

528
00:42:55,239 --> 00:42:57,198
You think you did
that by yourself?

529
00:42:58,409 --> 00:43:00,410
There was nobody else
up there with me.

530
00:43:00,494 --> 00:43:02,537
There was, Pete.
There was?

531
00:43:02,663 --> 00:43:06,833
There was someone like you.
Behind him was someone else.

532
00:43:07,418 --> 00:43:11,588
Maybe someone who learned
what he learned on a motorized box kite.

533
00:43:12,381 --> 00:43:16,718
And you knew that,
though you had a different word for it.

534
00:43:17,345 --> 00:43:19,429
I did? What word?

535
00:43:20,139 --> 00:43:22,265
It's what fliers
and piano players

536
00:43:22,350 --> 00:43:27,854
and everyone else count on.
They reach for it. They pray for it.

537
00:43:28,481 --> 00:43:31,983
And often, just when
they need it most, they get it.

538
00:43:32,568 --> 00:43:34,486
It's breathed into them.

539
00:43:35,279 --> 00:43:38,198
It's what the word means.
Spiritus.

540
00:43:38,824 --> 00:43:42,077
The divine breath.
Inspiration.

541
00:43:42,703 --> 00:43:44,496
Inspiration.

542
00:43:46,582 --> 00:43:48,917
And now it's your
turn to give it back.

543
00:43:50,336 --> 00:43:52,128
That's how
the whole thing works.

544
00:43:53,339 --> 00:43:55,131
That's how the
whole thing works.

545
00:43:55,424 --> 00:43:58,301
So now I'm supposed
to give inspiration to some flyer?

546
00:43:58,803 --> 00:44:01,805
Yes, but you're
not going back as a flying instructor.

547
00:44:03,933 --> 00:44:05,517
That's only part of it.

548
00:44:07,978 --> 00:44:10,563
How does this
work if I'm...

549
00:44:13,442 --> 00:44:15,985
They hear you inside
their own minds,

550
00:44:16,362 --> 00:44:19,280
as if it were their
thoughts. Clever?

551
00:44:20,908 --> 00:44:22,033
Clever.

552
00:44:22,451 --> 00:44:24,035
But remember, Pete.

553
00:44:24,787 --> 00:44:27,664
You've had your life,
for better or for worse.

554
00:44:28,499 --> 00:44:32,502
Anything you do
for yourself now is a waste of spirit.

555
00:44:33,963 --> 00:44:35,547
There's your boy.

556
00:44:36,966 --> 00:44:38,633
(WHIRRING)

557
00:45:20,718 --> 00:45:21,843
Hi.

558
00:45:28,225 --> 00:45:29,350
Hey, Rachel.

559
00:45:29,977 --> 00:45:31,186
Hi, buddy.

560
00:45:31,270 --> 00:45:32,562
(HUMMING)

561
00:45:38,611 --> 00:45:40,153
Why are you so happy?

562
00:45:41,280 --> 00:45:44,866
I think you're a pretty
silly-looking guy. What do you think of that?

563
00:46:10,976 --> 00:46:14,354
It has a mind of its own.
A glitch in the transmission.

564
00:46:15,940 --> 00:46:17,190
Are you Baker?
Yeah.

565
00:46:18,108 --> 00:46:19,442
The boss wants
to see you.

566
00:46:19,568 --> 00:46:20,777
Thanks. Where?

567
00:46:21,904 --> 00:46:23,988
To the right of
where it says, "Women."

568
00:46:24,073 --> 00:46:25,490
Green door.

569
00:46:26,325 --> 00:46:27,450
Thanks.

570
00:46:28,911 --> 00:46:30,328
I'm the "Women."

571
00:46:33,624 --> 00:46:36,834
First thing you have
to know is what type of plane you're flying.

572
00:46:37,002 --> 00:46:39,587
That determines
how many drops you can make.

573
00:46:40,130 --> 00:46:42,966
In our example,
we have an eight-door aircraft...

574
00:46:43,384 --> 00:46:45,385
Looking for
the training school? Yes.

575
00:46:46,011 --> 00:46:48,096
See the base
commander next door.

576
00:46:49,473 --> 00:46:50,807
(SCATTING)

577
00:46:54,687 --> 00:46:57,272
Al, you son
of a bitch, you!

578
00:46:58,274 --> 00:47:00,358
Jeez, you look great!

579
00:47:01,443 --> 00:47:06,573
I mean, you look
terrible in the same old great way.

580
00:47:06,907 --> 00:47:09,075
Honor to meet you,
sir. Ted Baker.

581
00:47:11,704 --> 00:47:13,288
Sorry I'm late.

582
00:47:15,541 --> 00:47:16,833
Did you get lost?

583
00:47:18,836 --> 00:47:20,211
Yes, I did.

584
00:47:20,462 --> 00:47:21,504
How did you know?

585
00:47:21,630 --> 00:47:22,672
It says here you
got your ticket back

586
00:47:22,756 --> 00:47:25,341
after a 12-month
suspension.

587
00:47:26,635 --> 00:47:29,220
While they looked
into why you flew 500 kitchen units...

588
00:47:29,388 --> 00:47:31,514
There's a crawly
thing on your face.

589
00:47:32,182 --> 00:47:35,059
Don't you want to
scratch your cheek? Its legs are tickling you.

590
00:47:35,269 --> 00:47:38,646
You mixed up Burbank
with Van Nuys.

591
00:47:39,273 --> 00:47:41,983
Lymers.
It's a little Lyme tick.

592
00:47:42,067 --> 00:47:45,361
My directional
gyro wasn't working.

593
00:47:45,446 --> 00:47:48,156
They're burrowing in.
They're laying eggs.

594
00:47:48,407 --> 00:47:50,116
You also violated
military air space.

595
00:47:50,367 --> 00:47:52,535
Try this.
It'll feel good.

596
00:47:54,538 --> 00:47:56,289
There you go.

597
00:47:56,957 --> 00:47:58,374
I'm going to
like this job.

598
00:47:58,667 --> 00:48:00,710
Sir, you have
a smudge on your face.

599
00:48:01,003 --> 00:48:02,003
Here?

600
00:48:02,296 --> 00:48:03,504
The other side.

601
00:48:03,631 --> 00:48:04,714
Right there.

602
00:48:13,223 --> 00:48:14,641
Another comedian.

603
00:48:15,059 --> 00:48:16,309
I'm not a comedian.

604
00:48:16,477 --> 00:48:17,769
You better not be.

605
00:48:18,062 --> 00:48:19,646
I feel so alive!

606
00:48:19,730 --> 00:48:21,105
Let me light that
for you.

607
00:48:30,407 --> 00:48:31,532
(GASPS)

608
00:48:31,617 --> 00:48:32,742
(CROWD LAUGHING)

609
00:48:43,921 --> 00:48:45,254
It's okay.

610
00:48:46,256 --> 00:48:48,675
Probably a cross wind
over the trash can.

611
00:48:51,887 --> 00:48:55,431
Kid, I think
we're both making a big mistake.

612
00:48:56,100 --> 00:49:00,019
Why don't you try again
with Wing 'N' Prayer?

613
00:49:00,104 --> 00:49:04,148
That was an air
delivery service. I was ahead of my time.

614
00:49:04,400 --> 00:49:05,692
You're that guy!

615
00:49:07,277 --> 00:49:08,778
That's why I'm here.

616
00:49:08,904 --> 00:49:11,948
I've never seen an
operation like this before. I like the smell of it.

617
00:49:12,449 --> 00:49:13,449
The smoke?

618
00:49:13,534 --> 00:49:14,617
That, too.

619
00:49:15,452 --> 00:49:17,870
I knew that was
what I wanted to do.

620
00:49:20,708 --> 00:49:21,708
I don't know.

621
00:49:21,792 --> 00:49:23,668
Give him a chance!

622
00:49:23,752 --> 00:49:26,045
Okay, you've got a chance.
Don't screw it up.

623
00:49:26,463 --> 00:49:28,423
Thank you, sir.

624
00:49:32,886 --> 00:49:34,220
(PANTING)

625
00:49:49,653 --> 00:49:53,114
Look at that bum.
He thinks he is on vacation.

626
00:49:56,034 --> 00:49:57,076
(MUSIC PLAYS)

627
00:49:57,161 --> 00:49:58,411
AL: Go.

628
00:49:59,371 --> 00:50:00,371
Go.

629
00:50:08,505 --> 00:50:10,298
Tune it. Tune it.

630
00:50:11,675 --> 00:50:12,800
Beautiful.

631
00:50:13,218 --> 00:50:15,136
(MAN SINGING ON RADIO)

632
00:50:19,266 --> 00:50:22,477
C-119 Transport,
this is Al the Pal.

633
00:50:23,687 --> 00:50:25,271
Let the games begin.

634
00:50:28,233 --> 00:50:29,233
(SUCKING)

635
00:50:32,654 --> 00:50:34,238
Right on.

636
00:50:34,865 --> 00:50:36,491
Looking good.

637
00:50:46,668 --> 00:50:48,878
Pitiful.

638
00:50:49,421 --> 00:50:51,047
It's a little premature.

639
00:50:54,635 --> 00:50:56,886
Bring it in, Powerhouse.

640
00:50:58,055 --> 00:51:00,097
That's it. Beautiful.

641
00:51:00,557 --> 00:51:02,725
Bring that fat
bomber in here.

642
00:51:06,063 --> 00:51:08,481
Drop! Drop!

643
00:51:12,069 --> 00:51:13,861
I'm glad we're not at war.

644
00:51:17,866 --> 00:51:20,117
Ted Baker, show time.
Hit it.

645
00:51:23,080 --> 00:51:24,997
Bad line, Ted.
Bad line!

646
00:51:25,165 --> 00:51:27,917
If you don't
straighten out, you'll dump all over Al.

647
00:51:30,504 --> 00:51:31,879
Great line, Ted.

648
00:51:38,262 --> 00:51:41,430
Aim for the flag that
looks like an umbrella.

649
00:51:45,936 --> 00:51:48,855
I'm sorry, Hap,
I can't help it. What the hell?

650
00:51:54,778 --> 00:51:55,987
Oh, my God!

651
00:52:00,534 --> 00:52:01,826
Nuts.

652
00:52:04,496 --> 00:52:05,621
Whoa!

653
00:52:15,883 --> 00:52:18,759
You'll find
your fortune falling

654
00:52:19,469 --> 00:52:21,304
All over town

655
00:52:21,430 --> 00:52:22,889
Is this first place?

656
00:52:28,395 --> 00:52:30,646
You must have showers

657
00:52:47,205 --> 00:52:48,414
Cute.

658
00:52:49,666 --> 00:52:51,584
Now we know
how ready you are.

659
00:52:53,253 --> 00:52:55,421
Fire season will
be here soon.

660
00:52:56,506 --> 00:52:58,382
If we get a real big one,

661
00:52:58,467 --> 00:53:00,885
they'll be calling guys
from all over. They'll be...

662
00:53:00,969 --> 00:53:03,679
...calling veterans,
first-timers,

663
00:53:04,348 --> 00:53:06,557
guys from all
over the country.

664
00:53:07,684 --> 00:53:10,436
When they call me and
say, "What've you got?"

665
00:53:12,272 --> 00:53:14,357
I'll tell them
I've got nothing

666
00:53:15,567 --> 00:53:18,653
because you're nothing.
What you did today was nothing.

667
00:53:18,862 --> 00:53:22,365
You can't hit
a smoking oil drum and a drum ain't a tree!

668
00:53:22,991 --> 00:53:25,242
A tree can explode
like a bomb!

669
00:53:26,370 --> 00:53:28,454
It can go up
like a Roman candle.

670
00:53:28,747 --> 00:53:31,874
An oil drum has no heat.
In a real fire, there is heat.

671
00:53:32,209 --> 00:53:35,586
There's heat that
can suck you under, flip you over.

672
00:53:36,672 --> 00:53:39,882
There are currents
that tie knots in a windsock. And, Baker...

673
00:53:41,551 --> 00:53:42,969
You're on the bus.

674
00:53:43,053 --> 00:53:46,222
When I get back from
San Diego tomorrow, I want you gone.

675
00:53:46,682 --> 00:53:48,099
Come on, Al.

676
00:53:48,558 --> 00:53:50,184
I didn't say anything.

677
00:53:51,687 --> 00:53:52,895
Good.

678
00:53:53,021 --> 00:53:56,232
It wasn't his fault.
Tell him it wasn't your fault.

679
00:53:57,025 --> 00:53:58,150
Where are you going?

680
00:53:58,151 --> 00:53:58,526
Where are you going?

681
00:54:00,028 --> 00:54:02,989
Don't quit.
I didn't come back to inspire a quitter.

682
00:54:03,073 --> 00:54:05,366
He'll cool off once
his color is normal.

683
00:54:05,534 --> 00:54:08,202
Party's over for me.
Forget that. This is your farewell party.

684
00:54:08,412 --> 00:54:11,330
Saddle up.
We're going to hit the bright lights.

685
00:54:27,097 --> 00:54:28,681
I think she likes you.

686
00:54:33,061 --> 00:54:34,353
Oh, Ted.

687
00:54:35,439 --> 00:54:36,605
(SIGHS)

688
00:54:38,275 --> 00:54:41,861
I met the most important
girl of my life in a bar like this.

689
00:54:42,487 --> 00:54:43,738
It's true.

690
00:54:45,407 --> 00:54:49,243
I took one look
at her and I said, "This is it."

691
00:54:49,619 --> 00:54:53,164
I went up to her and
I looked in her eyes,

692
00:54:54,082 --> 00:54:55,374
and I said,

693
00:54:56,126 --> 00:54:59,295
"You are the reason
that I am here."

694
00:55:02,090 --> 00:55:03,215
What'll it be?

695
00:55:03,467 --> 00:55:05,593
Vodka martini.
Don't forget the olive.

696
00:55:05,719 --> 00:55:07,803
Root beer.
Don't forget the olive.

697
00:55:32,037 --> 00:55:33,496
Hello, Ted.

698
00:55:35,207 --> 00:55:36,290
We'll miss you.

699
00:55:36,416 --> 00:55:37,500
"You're the reason
I'm here."

700
00:55:37,751 --> 00:55:39,335
Can I buy you a drink?

701
00:55:39,544 --> 00:55:41,504
Sure.
Bartender.

702
00:55:43,048 --> 00:55:44,340
Diet Pepsi.

703
00:55:44,549 --> 00:55:46,175
With or without
the olive?

704
00:55:46,301 --> 00:55:48,385
With or without...

705
00:55:49,262 --> 00:55:51,806
I think without.

706
00:55:52,891 --> 00:55:53,933
Thank you.

707
00:55:54,101 --> 00:55:56,602
Dance with her.
She wants to dance with you.

708
00:55:56,686 --> 00:55:58,771
Don't you have
any impulses?

709
00:55:59,356 --> 00:56:00,606
Dance?

710
00:56:02,025 --> 00:56:03,901
Sure, I'd love to.

711
00:56:05,320 --> 00:56:06,695
Love to what?

712
00:56:08,448 --> 00:56:09,949
Did you say "dance"?

713
00:56:11,284 --> 00:56:12,535
Did I? I can't dance.

714
00:56:12,619 --> 00:56:14,120
(CHUCKLES)

715
00:56:16,039 --> 00:56:17,414
Talking is nice.

716
00:56:17,582 --> 00:56:19,542
I'm not a good
talker either.

717
00:56:19,918 --> 00:56:21,544
This is nice.

718
00:56:23,588 --> 00:56:24,713
It is?

719
00:56:25,924 --> 00:56:27,550
Don't you think so?

720
00:56:31,012 --> 00:56:32,304
Rachel?

721
00:56:33,723 --> 00:56:36,892
Do you think
it's possible to see a girl

722
00:56:38,520 --> 00:56:42,356
and know right off
that she is it?

723
00:56:47,904 --> 00:56:49,864
I think it's possible.

724
00:56:51,575 --> 00:56:53,659
This is hard
to talk about.

725
00:56:54,911 --> 00:56:56,412
Try.

726
00:56:58,248 --> 00:56:59,415
It's happened to me.

727
00:56:59,749 --> 00:57:01,834
I think you're
overdoing this.

728
00:57:02,335 --> 00:57:03,586
It has?

729
00:57:05,005 --> 00:57:06,589
It was last summer.

730
00:57:07,507 --> 00:57:10,718
I only saw her once.
I wish you could have met her.

731
00:57:11,511 --> 00:57:14,638
It's like reading a book,
and after the first page,

732
00:57:14,931 --> 00:57:17,892
you know how
it will turn out. It was like that.

733
00:57:20,103 --> 00:57:21,687
That's why I'm here.

734
00:57:22,189 --> 00:57:25,316
It feels good to
tell somebody that. Thank you.

735
00:57:28,111 --> 00:57:30,362
Well, I think I'll just...

736
00:57:32,782 --> 00:57:34,200
...come in again.

737
00:57:37,495 --> 00:57:40,831
Rachel, what
about your drink? He's bringing your drink.

738
00:57:41,833 --> 00:57:43,918
I don't think I've
ever come across

739
00:57:44,002 --> 00:57:46,003
this particular
technique before.

740
00:57:49,090 --> 00:57:51,008
(COUNTRY MUSIC PLAYING)

741
00:58:00,227 --> 00:58:03,896
First approach,
this is Cessna Skymaster 5-2-1-0 Kilo.

742
00:58:04,856 --> 00:58:06,941
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATION)

743
00:58:14,824 --> 00:58:16,242
Roger, 1-0 Kilo.

744
00:58:16,868 --> 00:58:19,912
DORINDA: Squawk 0-2-4-7,
maintain 5,500.

745
00:58:20,497 --> 00:58:21,664
Say again.

746
00:58:21,790 --> 00:58:23,832
1-0 Kilo...
Dorinda?

747
00:58:25,710 --> 00:58:27,211
Honey bunny?

748
00:58:27,671 --> 00:58:29,546
You little quarter-pounder,
is that you?

749
00:58:32,217 --> 00:58:34,802
Lamb chop, what are
you doing here?

750
00:58:35,303 --> 00:58:36,679
Coast approach, baby.

751
00:58:37,097 --> 00:58:39,890
Request immediate
rendezvous upon landing.

752
00:58:42,519 --> 00:58:44,436
(MIMICKING JULIA
CHILD) Welcome. (AUDIENCE LAUGH)

753
00:58:44,521 --> 00:58:46,438
I'm Julia Child.

754
00:58:47,065 --> 00:58:49,692
Today we're going to make
a holiday feast or

755
00:58:49,776 --> 00:58:51,735
le fete d'holiday.

756
00:58:52,237 --> 00:58:55,447
We're going to start
with half-boned chicken or poularde,

757
00:58:55,740 --> 00:58:57,658
demi des Francais.

758
00:58:59,536 --> 00:59:01,287
To bone the chicken,

759
00:59:01,371 --> 00:59:04,456
you need
a very sharp knife.

760
00:59:04,541 --> 00:59:06,875
You can't do nothing
without a very sharp knife.

761
00:59:07,294 --> 00:59:10,504
Now I've done it.
I cut the dickens out of my finger.

762
00:59:11,172 --> 00:59:12,339
I'm glad in a way
this happened.

763
00:59:12,424 --> 00:59:15,968
Accidents do occur
from time to time in the kitchen.

764
00:59:17,470 --> 00:59:19,013
(PLANE FLYING)

765
00:59:20,640 --> 00:59:22,391
Have you been
here long, kid?

766
00:59:23,101 --> 00:59:24,226
Huh?

767
00:59:24,352 --> 00:59:25,644
Been here long?

768
00:59:25,895 --> 00:59:27,646
Not so long.

769
00:59:27,731 --> 00:59:30,691
I've been doing standby
at the tower for about a month.

770
00:59:31,067 --> 00:59:33,152
It's just holiday relief.

771
00:59:43,204 --> 00:59:44,413
Can I use your phone?

772
00:59:44,497 --> 00:59:45,664
Yes.

773
01:00:04,017 --> 01:00:05,476
535 please.

774
01:00:06,978 --> 01:00:09,605
Frank, this is Al Yackey.
I'm the guy that was

775
01:00:09,689 --> 01:00:11,732
over this morning
looking for

776
01:00:11,816 --> 01:00:13,859
the Skymaster that
was being retired.

777
01:00:14,361 --> 01:00:16,445
You said I could
check it out as soon as

778
01:00:16,571 --> 01:00:18,655
I found a pilot to
fly it to Flat Rock.

779
01:00:19,908 --> 01:00:24,370
I found a guy.
I'll be over in an hour to take it off your hands.

780
01:00:25,705 --> 01:00:27,456
I'll bring
the guy with me.

781
01:00:30,335 --> 01:00:31,794
What are you doing?

782
01:00:35,256 --> 01:00:37,800
I'm taking you back
to Flat Rock with me.

783
01:00:38,843 --> 01:00:40,552
I can't go.
Why?

784
01:00:40,804 --> 01:00:41,970
Because...

785
01:00:46,267 --> 01:00:47,851
...I'm here now.

