dance with you, but... Yeah.

918
01:12:22,296 --> 01:12:23,338
Happy days.

919
01:12:23,422 --> 01:12:24,464
You're here again!

920
01:12:24,590 --> 01:12:28,343
Are you all right?
I'll have the fence fixed, I swear.

921
01:12:28,427 --> 01:12:30,845
You never told me
life was so exciting.

922
01:12:31,222 --> 01:12:33,223
I can explain everything.

923
01:12:34,475 --> 01:12:35,683
No, I can't.

924
01:12:35,851 --> 01:12:37,060
People always
dropping in.

925
01:12:37,394 --> 01:12:40,396
Why are you still here?
I told you to leave.

926
01:12:42,399 --> 01:12:44,859
He likes you.
He doesn't like anybody.

927
01:12:45,486 --> 01:12:47,070
Is this your cat?
Yes.

928
01:12:47,780 --> 01:12:49,030
What's his name?

929
01:12:49,115 --> 01:12:50,365
Linda Blair.

930
01:12:51,450 --> 01:12:53,868
(LAUGHING)

931
01:12:58,249 --> 01:13:00,041
You laugh
like a donkey.

932
01:13:00,292 --> 01:13:02,377
I like it. I...

933
01:13:03,379 --> 01:13:05,130
...used to know
a donkey.

934
01:13:05,881 --> 01:13:07,257
Why are you still here?

935
01:13:07,424 --> 01:13:11,261
Al, do you remember
Ted Baker? Ted, this is Al Yackey.

936
01:13:14,974 --> 01:13:16,224
How have you been?

937
01:13:18,477 --> 01:13:20,395
I'm stupid. You guys...

938
01:13:20,980 --> 01:13:22,772
You must be one
of Al's pilots.

939
01:13:23,732 --> 01:13:24,732
I was.

940
01:13:24,859 --> 01:13:26,442
That's a nice surprise.

941
01:13:27,027 --> 01:13:28,236
Isn't it?

942
01:13:31,657 --> 01:13:33,575
Yes, isn't it?
Indeed it is.

943
01:13:34,076 --> 01:13:36,536
Yes, Baker is one
of the boys.

944
01:13:36,954 --> 01:13:38,454
I am?
Yes.

945
01:13:38,581 --> 01:13:40,623
The lad shows
a lot of promise. I do?

946
01:13:40,958 --> 01:13:44,836
Dorinda is one of the
toughest fire-fighting babes you'll ever see.

947
01:13:44,920 --> 01:13:46,171
And funny.

948
01:13:46,463 --> 01:13:48,464
