1042
01:19:04,072 --> 01:19:05,239
Call an ambulance!

1043
01:19:09,077 --> 01:19:10,578
(CHILDREN
TALKING INDISTINCTLY)

1044
01:19:12,915 --> 01:19:16,042
Well, Frank is sick
and I'll try to help him.

1045
01:19:16,126 --> 01:19:19,003
Tell me your names.
Who's first?

1046
01:19:19,630 --> 01:19:20,671
Mario.

1047
01:19:20,756 --> 01:19:21,881
Todd.

1048
01:19:21,965 --> 01:19:23,257
Ascensión.

1049
01:19:23,383 --> 01:19:25,468
(CHILDREN CONTINUE TALKING)

1050
01:19:28,305 --> 01:19:30,723
All right,
what do you want to be when you grow up?

1051
01:19:31,141 --> 01:19:33,184
I want to work
on Wall Street.

1052
01:19:33,560 --> 01:19:37,438
Wall Street?
I never had good enough grades to work on Wall Street.

1053
01:19:40,859 --> 01:19:42,735
What about you, Mario?

1054
01:19:43,737 --> 01:19:45,780
MARIO: I want
to be an astronaut.

1055
01:19:46,198 --> 01:19:48,324
GIRL: I want
to be a veterinarian.

1056
01:19:48,408 --> 01:19:50,159
BOY: I want to be
a football player.

1057
01:19:59,253 --> 01:20:01,837
You did real good,
stopping that bus before you died.

1058
01:20:11,807 --> 01:20:14,600
Come on, kid.
You can do it.

1059
01:20:16,937 --> 01:20:19,230
I have to go
to the bathroom.

1060
01:20:19,898 --> 01:20:22,316
I have to go
to the bathroom, too. Come on, Frank.

1061
01:20:24,027 --> 01:20:25,027
(GASPS)

1062
01:20:30,325 --> 01:20:32,493
Hey, you made it!

1063
01:20:33,161 --> 01:20:34,870
(CHILDREN CHEERING)

1064
01:20:47,134 --> 01:20:48,884
(UPBEAT SONG PLAYING)

1065
01:21:51,573 --> 01:21:52,990
(WHIRRING)

1066
01:22:25,607 --> 01:22:26,774
Hi.
Hi.

1067
01:22:28,235 --> 01:22:29,777
Come in.
Thanks.

1068
01:22:32,656 --> 01:22:34,532
Holy cow,
look at this.

1069
01:22:34,616 --> 01:22:35,700
Yeah.

1070
01:22:35,784 --> 01:22:37,118
(CHUCKLES)

1071
01:22:38,412 --> 01:22:40,371
You've been busy.
Kind of.

1072
01:22:40,831 --> 01:22:42,331
I had no idea.

1073
01:22:44,960 --> 01:22:48,129
Everything smells great.
Look what you've done.

1074
01:22:48,255 --> 01:22:49,964
She can't do toast.

1075
01:22:50,882 --> 01:22:53,884
You've got a little
mashed potatoes right...

1076
01:22:54,761 --> 01:22:55,761
Oh. (CHUCKLES)

1077
01:22:58,140 --> 01:22:59,515
Oh, look at me.

1078
01:22:59,641 --> 01:23:02,393
Uh, let me go get
myself fixed up.

1079
01:23:03,979 --> 01:23:06,939
There's something
fishy here and it's not the chicken.

1080
01:23:10,861 --> 01:23:13,404
Then there was the time
he delivered a PBY to

1081
01:23:13,739 --> 01:23:16,866
to Michigan or Mexico.
Know what a PBY is?

1082
01:23:16,950 --> 01:23:18,868
Ketchup?
Sure.

1083
01:23:18,952 --> 01:23:21,120
He's taking off
in this PBY,

1084
01:23:21,204 --> 01:23:24,331
which is a feat in itself.
They're amazing planes.

1085
01:23:24,416 --> 01:23:26,709
TED: It's like
a tugboat with wings.

1086
01:23:27,252 --> 01:23:29,253
Do they only feed
you every two weeks?

1087
01:23:29,337 --> 01:23:30,963
What was I
talking about?

1088
01:23:31,882 --> 01:23:33,132
Pete, still.

1089
01:23:33,216 --> 01:23:36,343
So he's flying this PBY
when he sees this fire.

1090
01:23:36,428 --> 01:23:37,428
Forest fire.
Uh-uh.

1091
01:23:37,512 --> 01:23:39,680
Main Street.
Village grocery store.

1092
01:23:39,848 --> 01:23:42,057
The nearest fire engine
is 20 miles away.

1093
01:23:42,184 --> 01:23:43,434
Oh, you can
pick up the chicken.

1094
01:23:43,518 --> 01:23:44,727
Anything that flies,
it's okay.

1095
01:23:45,353 --> 01:23:46,687
Even in a
good restaurant.

1096
01:23:47,147 --> 01:23:48,272
Mmm-hmm.

1097
01:23:49,399 --> 01:23:54,320
He sees this building on fire
and outside of town is this reservoir.

1098
01:23:54,863 --> 01:23:56,071
So he...

1099
01:23:56,156 --> 01:23:59,742
Fills the plane with water
and dumps it on the fire.

1100
01:23:59,826 --> 01:24:03,454
No, he missed!
He hit the post office next door.

1101
01:24:03,538 --> 01:24:05,289
Took him three tries.
(LAUGHS)

1102
01:24:05,373 --> 01:24:08,459
The town was awash.
The groceries were burned.

1103
01:24:08,543 --> 01:24:11,128
It was fire,
flood and famine. If he'd managed

1104
01:24:11,213 --> 01:24:13,214
the plague, it would've
been the Four Horsemen

1105
01:24:13,298 --> 01:24:15,257
of the Apocalypse
in one PBY.

1106
01:24:15,717 --> 01:24:18,177
I mean, he was unique.

1107
01:24:22,057 --> 01:24:23,974
Why are you
plucking your eyebrows?

1108
01:24:25,227 --> 01:24:26,560
Oh, I didn't know I was.

1109
01:24:29,189 --> 01:24:31,440
Nervous habit.
Want to do the wishbone?

1110
01:24:31,525 --> 01:24:32,608
Sure.

1111
01:24:34,486 --> 01:24:36,111
Okay, here we go.

1112
01:24:41,159 --> 01:24:42,493
Your wish.

1113
01:24:46,706 --> 01:24:48,749
He was up in that plane,

1114
01:24:51,878 --> 01:24:53,879
doing his dumb stunts.

1115
01:24:57,384 --> 01:24:59,093
There would be this
tone in his voice.

1116
01:24:59,177 --> 01:25:00,886
I called it his
"Evel Knievel" voice.

1117
01:25:01,304 --> 01:25:04,223
I don't know who he was
when he sounded like that.

1118
01:25:04,307 --> 01:25:05,975
Part of you thought
it was great.

1119
01:25:06,059 --> 01:25:08,185
DORINDA: What did
he think I thought?

1120
01:25:09,437 --> 01:25:11,146
Was he dumb
enough to think

1121
01:25:12,774 --> 01:25:16,193
I admired him for it?
For flying like that?

1122
01:25:16,319 --> 01:25:17,945
(SIGHS) Okay.

1123
01:25:18,697 --> 01:25:19,822
Do you think?

1124
01:25:20,448 --> 01:25:21,949
I wasn't there.

1125
01:25:25,620 --> 01:25:28,080
I shouldn't be
talking about this.

1126
01:25:29,457 --> 01:25:30,958
Some birthday.

1127
01:25:32,627 --> 01:25:33,794
It's your birthday?

1128
01:25:33,879 --> 01:25:35,004
No, it's yours.

1129
01:25:35,088 --> 01:25:36,505
No, it isn't.

1130
01:25:37,132 --> 01:25:39,633
Since it was your birthday
this time last year,

1131
01:25:39,718 --> 01:25:41,802
it should be
this year, too. No, no.

1132
01:25:42,762 --> 01:25:45,180
Pete remembered
my birthday wrong.

1133
01:25:49,227 --> 01:25:51,020
It's a year tomorrow.

1134
01:25:52,606 --> 01:25:54,398
TED:
It's a year tomorrow.

1135
01:25:54,816 --> 01:25:55,983
A year?

1136
01:25:57,485 --> 01:26:00,362
I saw him land
a plane once. I saw him dance.

1137
01:26:00,655 --> 01:26:02,239
He had his own
way of doing both.

1138
01:26:02,324 --> 01:26:03,741
He could drive an A-26
around the sky.

1139
01:26:03,825 --> 01:26:05,200
He wasn't dumb.

1140
01:26:05,327 --> 01:26:09,079
You were impressed that
he brought that A-26 in on an empty tank.

1141
01:26:09,164 --> 01:26:10,664
You try it.

1142
01:26:10,790 --> 01:26:12,333
When I do,
I'll have the height.

1143
01:26:12,542 --> 01:26:13,918
I'd like to be there.

1144
01:26:14,002 --> 01:26:15,419
I want you
to be there.

1145
01:26:18,882 --> 01:26:20,883
What are you doing to me?

1146
01:26:24,179 --> 01:26:25,930
Trying to
confuse you, I hope.

1147
01:26:26,514 --> 01:26:27,765
You are.

1148
01:26:31,728 --> 01:26:34,688
You never thought
you'd dance again, did you?

1149
01:26:39,986 --> 01:26:41,195
I guess.

1150
01:26:43,615 --> 01:26:45,366
Shh! Hear that?

1151
01:26:46,534 --> 01:26:47,660
What?

1152
01:26:52,207 --> 01:26:53,832
There's no music.

1153
01:26:56,628 --> 01:26:57,711
(CHUCKLES)

1154
01:27:01,716 --> 01:27:03,509
That's my girl, pal.

1155
01:27:09,224 --> 01:27:11,016
Yes, put that one on.

1156
01:27:12,435 --> 01:27:13,894
Fast forward.

1157
01:27:14,896 --> 01:27:15,938
Keep going.

1158
01:27:16,022 --> 01:27:17,064
(WHIRRING)

1159
01:27:17,148 --> 01:27:18,399
Keep going.

1160
01:27:18,942 --> 01:27:20,317
Keep going.

1161
01:27:21,236 --> 01:27:22,277
No, don't stop.

1162
01:27:22,404 --> 01:27:23,487
(ROMANTIC SONG PLAYING)

1163
01:27:58,648 --> 01:28:00,065
Left rudder.

1164
01:28:09,451 --> 01:28:11,660
TED: I think
you got me all wrong.

1165
01:28:12,579 --> 01:28:15,456
You invited me
because I'm a safe guy

1166
01:28:15,540 --> 01:28:17,833
who will play along with
your memories of Pete.

1167
01:28:18,626 --> 01:28:20,544
I don't have any
memories of Pete.

1168
01:28:20,628 --> 01:28:22,087
I have memories
of my own,

1169
01:28:22,172 --> 01:28:24,840
but I don't let them get
in the way of my life.

1170
01:28:49,324 --> 01:28:51,325
(SOBS) Oh, Hap!

1171
01:28:53,411 --> 01:28:56,413
Please! Please,
take me out of here.

1172
01:28:59,751 --> 01:29:01,460
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

1173
01:29:14,099 --> 01:29:15,349
(SIGHS)

1174
01:29:15,517 --> 01:29:16,725
(ROMANTIC SONG PLAYING)

1175
01:29:31,699 --> 01:29:33,283
(CHUCKLES)

1176
01:29:39,290 --> 01:29:40,541
Can we...

1177
01:29:48,716 --> 01:29:51,552
...just finish this dance
some other time?

1178
01:29:57,934 --> 01:29:59,434
(MUSIC STOPS)

1179
01:30:06,776 --> 01:30:08,110
I'm sorry.

1180
01:30:10,905 --> 01:30:12,906
(MIMICKING JOHN WAYNE)
Sleep tight, baby sister.

1181
01:30:13,449 --> 01:30:14,741
(LAUGHS)

1182
01:30:17,871 --> 01:30:19,913
See you tomorrow.
I'll see you tomorrow.

1183
01:30:20,999 --> 01:30:22,332
(IMITATING JOHN WAYNE)
I'm going to see

1184
01:30:22,417 --> 01:30:24,209
if old Dollar's tied
to the hitching rail

1185
01:30:24,294 --> 01:30:27,963
and ride off
into the sunset by myself again.

1186
01:30:42,020 --> 01:30:43,854
(WHIRRING)

1187
01:30:46,941 --> 01:30:48,817
(ROMANTIC SONG PLAYING)

1188
01:31:29,984 --> 01:31:32,402
(WHISPERS) Can I
have this dance?

1189
01:32:33,840 --> 01:32:35,048
(BLOWS)

1190
01:32:39,971 --> 01:32:41,221
Lettuce.

1191
01:32:42,140 --> 01:32:43,390
Ketchup.

1192
01:32:44,475 --> 01:32:45,726
Peaches.

1193
01:32:48,229 --> 01:32:49,563
Cantaloupe.

1194
01:32:53,693 --> 01:32:54,776
Eggs.

1195
01:32:55,028 --> 01:32:56,903
PETE: You're shopping
in your sleep again.

1196
01:32:56,988 --> 01:32:58,488
DORINDA:
Peanut butter.

1197
01:33:02,076 --> 01:33:03,118
Gin.

1198
01:33:03,870 --> 01:33:05,787
Anything special for me?

1199
01:33:05,872 --> 01:33:07,831
Chlorine bleach. (MOANS)

1200
01:33:09,000 --> 01:33:10,375
Chap Stick.

1201
01:33:11,502 --> 01:33:12,836
Band-Aids.

1202
01:33:13,504 --> 01:33:15,505
You always made me laugh.

1203
01:33:17,842 --> 01:33:19,051
Uh-uh.

1204
01:33:21,429 --> 01:33:22,929
Yes, you did.

1205
01:33:26,142 --> 01:33:27,809
You never laughed.

1206
01:33:29,729 --> 01:33:31,813
I never laughed
at your jokes,

1207
01:33:31,898 --> 01:33:34,566
but you were
always very funny.

1208
01:33:35,109 --> 01:33:37,110
Liar, liar,
pants on fire.

1209
01:33:40,531 --> 01:33:42,949
I swear to God
I'll keep you safe.

1210
01:33:45,703 --> 01:33:47,788
I'll never
leave you again.

1211
01:33:52,377 --> 01:33:53,460
Yes.

1212
01:33:56,631 --> 01:33:58,423
Good night, Dorinda.

1213
01:34:01,010 --> 01:34:02,427
Night, Pete.

1214
01:34:24,075 --> 01:34:25,325
(GRUNTS)

1215
01:34:29,997 --> 01:34:31,331
(SIGHS)

1216
01:34:31,416 --> 01:34:33,750
Hap. How did
you get here?

1217
01:34:35,336 --> 01:34:38,463
I mean, how did I get here?

1218
01:34:39,757 --> 01:34:41,758
Mainly by the wrong road.

1219
01:34:41,884 --> 01:34:44,052
I told you,
your life is over

1220
01:34:44,137 --> 01:34:45,679
and anything you
do for yourself

1221
01:34:45,847 --> 01:34:47,389
is a waste of spirit,
remember?

1222
01:34:49,142 --> 01:34:50,725
Yes, I remember.

1223
01:34:53,020 --> 01:34:55,897
But you didn't tell me
everything, did you?

1224
01:34:57,608 --> 01:34:59,067
Do you know what
I've been going through?

1225
01:35:00,027 --> 01:35:01,069
Yes.

1226
01:35:01,821 --> 01:35:04,030
What do you want
from me, Hap?

1227
01:35:05,700 --> 01:35:08,618
If I'm really dead,
how come I hurt so bad?

1228
01:35:10,788 --> 01:35:12,747
What kind of deal is this?

1229
01:35:12,832 --> 01:35:15,500
You said I was going back
to be an inspiration.

1230
01:35:15,585 --> 01:35:18,545
You never said
I would feel what I'm feeling.

1231
01:35:18,629 --> 01:35:21,047
You didn't tell
me that I would...

1232
01:35:23,342 --> 01:35:24,885
...see Dorinda.

1233
01:35:27,054 --> 01:35:29,389
What do you
really want from me?

1234
01:35:42,320 --> 01:35:44,446
We gave you
a chance to say,

1235
01:35:44,572 --> 01:35:47,240
"I'm glad I lived.
I'm glad I was alive.

1236
01:35:47,325 --> 01:35:51,328
"Now it's my turn
to give you a hand. Let me give you what I had."

1237
01:35:52,747 --> 01:35:56,333
But I also sent you
back to settle with the one you love.

1238
01:35:57,376 --> 01:35:59,669
I sent you back
to say goodbye.

1239
01:36:01,297 --> 01:36:04,883
Until you do that,
she won't be free. And neither will you.

1240
01:36:09,430 --> 01:36:11,598
I'm not ready
to say goodbye.

1241
01:36:16,437 --> 01:36:18,647
You're such
a good man, Pete.

1242
01:36:19,315 --> 01:36:21,775
We don't send
back the other kind.

1243
01:36:22,235 --> 01:36:24,528
But you still
have to learn that

1244
01:36:24,612 --> 01:36:26,780
to gain your freedom,
you have to give it.

1245
01:36:27,823 --> 01:36:29,366
So go find out.

1246
01:36:32,370 --> 01:36:34,371
(PLANES ROARING OVERHEAD)

1247
01:36:34,455 --> 01:36:36,706
(FIREMEN TALKING INDISTINCTLY)

1248
01:36:40,294 --> 01:36:41,962
(ENGINE ROARING)

1249
01:36:51,472 --> 01:36:53,765
(FIREMEN TALKING INDISTINCTLY)

1250
01:37:00,940 --> 01:37:03,066
(INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER)

1251
01:37:10,741 --> 01:37:12,867
DORINDA:
Shake 'N' Bake, do you read?

1252
01:37:14,996 --> 01:37:17,747
Shake 'N' Bake,
this is Tanker Base. Do you read?

1253
01:37:17,832 --> 01:37:20,417
TED: I read you,
but I'm a little busy right now.

1254
01:37:20,501 --> 01:37:23,837
You've been up a long time.
How's your fuel reading?

1255
01:37:25,506 --> 01:37:27,007
How's your fuel?

1256
01:37:28,843 --> 01:37:30,844
Ted, leave your mike open.

1257
01:37:31,387 --> 01:37:32,929
(ENGINE SPUTTERING)

1258
01:37:33,014 --> 01:37:34,806
TED: Okay,
I'm coming in.

1259
01:37:35,182 --> 01:37:37,058
He is really low on fuel.

1260
01:37:39,353 --> 01:37:40,645
(PLANE APPROACHING)

1261
01:37:42,940 --> 01:37:44,524
(ALARM RINGING)

1262
01:38:08,174 --> 01:38:09,591
That's beautiful.

1263
01:38:09,717 --> 01:38:11,134
How'd you
teach him that?

1264
01:38:11,218 --> 01:38:15,138
You don't teach that.
He's got wings. Best I've seen since Pete.

1265
01:38:15,222 --> 01:38:16,640
What gives?

1266
01:38:16,766 --> 01:38:18,224
Baker coming in on
a wing and a prayer.

1267
01:38:18,309 --> 01:38:19,851
(SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE)

1268
01:38:19,935 --> 01:38:22,145
You gave my crew
30 seconds warning!

1269
01:38:22,229 --> 01:38:23,855
That's all I had.

1270
01:38:27,568 --> 01:38:28,735
Jesus.

1271
01:38:28,903 --> 01:38:30,737
Another damn hotshot.

1272
01:38:31,197 --> 01:38:33,073
Another by god hotshot.

1273
01:38:34,575 --> 01:38:35,992
FIREMAN: Right behind you!

1274
01:38:36,118 --> 01:38:37,577
(FIREMEN YELLING INDISTINCTLY)

1275
01:38:37,745 --> 01:38:39,913
(FIRE CRACKLING INTENSELY)

1276
01:38:44,001 --> 01:38:48,380
Round them up!
There's a cutback over here! Let's go!

1277
01:38:48,923 --> 01:38:51,132
(FIREMEN YELLING INDISTINCTLY)

1278
01:39:00,476 --> 01:39:01,768
(YAWNS)

1279
01:39:05,439 --> 01:39:06,773
(SIGHS)

1280
01:39:11,862 --> 01:39:14,447
MAN: Operations,
this is Smoke Jumper's squad boss!

1281
01:39:15,574 --> 01:39:17,158
Say again, over.

1282
01:39:18,119 --> 01:39:19,452
(FIREMEN YELLING INDISTINCTLY)

1283
01:39:19,578 --> 01:39:20,829
Mayday!
We have a major blowout!

1284
01:39:20,913 --> 01:39:22,997
Our escape route
has been cut off.

1285
01:39:23,082 --> 01:39:26,751
We're by the radio tower
on the south side of Dome Peak.

1286
01:39:27,670 --> 01:39:30,547
Our only escape route
is the gully to the southwest.

1287
01:39:31,507 --> 01:39:33,466
We're heading for
the Kootenai River.

1288
01:39:33,551 --> 01:39:36,845
I can see the waterfall
at the upper end of Bull Lake.

1289
01:39:37,805 --> 01:39:42,100
Get on the radio
to the heli-base. Have the choppers standing by.

1290
01:39:44,395 --> 01:39:46,646
Libby Operations
to Heli-base.

1291
01:39:46,814 --> 01:39:50,984
Ted, those choppers
are 40 miles away. They fly at 100 miles an hour.

1292
01:39:51,444 --> 01:39:53,403
Libby Operations
to Heli-base.

1293
01:39:53,487 --> 01:39:56,448
We're 12 miles away.
We fly at 220 miles an hour.

1294
01:39:58,242 --> 01:39:59,784
WOMAN: (OVER RADIO)
Libby Operations,

1295
01:39:59,910 --> 01:40:01,453
this is Heli-base.
We read. Over.

1296
01:40:03,330 --> 01:40:05,665
Air Attack, 6-3 Echo,
this is Operations.

1297
01:40:05,833 --> 01:40:08,126
We will handle
the incident from here.

1298
01:40:08,210 --> 01:40:11,588
Contact the Jumper boss
and ascertain their location.

1299
01:40:12,256 --> 01:40:13,631
Hey, Ted.

1300
01:40:14,341 --> 01:40:15,341
What are you doing?

1301
01:40:15,718 --> 01:40:18,178
Don't worry, Al.
I'll bring him back.

1302
01:40:19,013 --> 01:40:22,307
Nails, get me a WAC chart
and sectional for Dome Mountain.

1303
01:40:22,391 --> 01:40:24,768
Get everything
you've got together.

1304
01:40:24,852 --> 01:40:26,561
I'll take your plane.

1305
01:40:26,645 --> 01:40:28,271
It's my plane, I fly it.

1306
01:40:28,606 --> 01:40:32,275
We don't have time, Nails.

1307
01:40:32,526 --> 01:40:35,028
Get a load of mud and
fill it to the tabs. I'll need all of it.

1308
01:40:35,154 --> 01:40:37,822
Not even that
shithead Pete could pull this off.

1309
01:40:37,907 --> 01:40:41,159
But he would have tried.

1310
01:40:41,619 --> 01:40:43,077
I'll have your
license for this!

1311
01:40:43,162 --> 01:40:44,537
I work for the Department
of Agriculture...

1312
01:40:44,997 --> 01:40:46,539
(FIREMEN YELLING INDISTINCTLY)

1313
01:40:46,665 --> 01:40:48,208
(FIRE CRACKLING INTENSELY)

1314
01:40:58,385 --> 01:41:02,222
Alex, get up on that ridge
and see if we can get to the river!

1315
01:41:09,313 --> 01:41:10,522
MAN: Clear!

1316
01:41:17,571 --> 01:41:18,780
Dorinda.

1317
01:41:20,115 --> 01:41:22,408
You may want to
come down here.

1318
01:41:23,619 --> 01:41:26,204
We've got sort
of an emergency.

1319
01:41:26,872 --> 01:41:29,749
The wind shifted and
the smoke jumpers...

1320
01:41:32,503 --> 01:41:34,921
Ted is going to
fly into the gully above the waterfall.

1321
01:41:38,843 --> 01:41:41,177
Yes, honey,
it's dark here, too.

1322
01:41:42,304 --> 01:41:44,556
(FIREMEN YELLING INDISTINCTLY)

1323
01:41:54,567 --> 01:41:55,900
You okay?

1324
01:41:56,277 --> 01:41:57,443
I see the water.

1325
01:41:58,320 --> 01:41:59,529
But there's a firestorm
on the ridge.

1326
01:42:21,802 --> 01:42:24,888
Find out where they're heading
then show me on the map.

1327
01:42:24,972 --> 01:42:27,390
How strong are
the winds on the fire?

1328
01:42:27,975 --> 01:42:30,101
How about some coordinates?

1329
01:43:11,769 --> 01:43:13,853
Powerhouse!

1330
01:43:14,480 --> 01:43:16,356
I'd like to be
in on this one.

1331
01:43:16,649 --> 01:43:19,484
You might get to.
Al wants to see you.

1332
01:43:20,069 --> 01:43:21,235
Great!

1333
01:43:21,695 --> 01:43:23,613
Don't cut it.

1334
01:43:23,697 --> 01:43:25,531
I'll hold it for you.

1335
01:44:12,037 --> 01:44:15,123
Winds from the southwest,
40 knots and gusting.

1336
01:44:15,374 --> 01:44:16,833
(PLANE ENGINE WHIRRING)

1337
01:44:33,100 --> 01:44:35,184
Dorinda, you throttle
back and return

1338
01:44:35,269 --> 01:44:37,353
that plane to
the ramp right now.

1339
01:44:38,230 --> 01:44:42,650
Honey, we got six poor guys
out there and I need 59 here, right now.

1340
01:44:55,456 --> 01:44:59,125
I don't know
what you're doing, but turn this plane around.

1341
01:44:59,752 --> 01:45:01,711
You never would
listen to me

1342
01:45:01,837 --> 01:45:03,755
and you've always done
fine, but this isn't the same.

1343
01:45:03,839 --> 01:45:06,299
This is Ted's mission
and you're not good enough.

1344
01:45:07,426 --> 01:45:10,762
You won't make it.
Is that what you want?

1345
01:45:12,306 --> 01:45:14,057
That's not my girl.

1346
01:45:14,224 --> 01:45:17,310
Damn it, Dorinda!
This is no time to dick around...

1347
01:45:17,686 --> 01:45:18,811
...with an airplane!

1348
01:45:33,827 --> 01:45:35,828
Let's not be rational.

1349
01:45:36,413 --> 01:45:37,663
Throttle.

1350
01:45:38,165 --> 01:45:39,916
More throttle.

1351
01:45:45,506 --> 01:45:48,299
Level out. Level out!

1352
01:45:49,551 --> 01:45:53,387
And you say I flew crazy?
What are you doing? Fly smart.

1353
01:45:53,764 --> 01:45:55,181
Those guys need you.

1354
01:45:59,019 --> 01:46:00,853
I hear it!

1355
01:46:01,522 --> 01:46:03,648
If you've got
water, use it!

1356
01:46:07,528 --> 01:46:09,612
Did you see that flare?
There they are.

1357
01:46:09,738 --> 01:46:11,823
Make a path for
them to the river.

1358
01:46:13,367 --> 01:46:15,952
Ride it.
Ride it, Dorinda.

1359
01:46:18,747 --> 01:46:20,706
Slip right. Slip right.

1360
01:46:20,874 --> 01:46:22,166
(GRUNTS)

1361
01:46:23,043 --> 01:46:25,461
Use the crosswind.
Right rudder.

1362
01:46:27,548 --> 01:46:29,549
Here we go. Come on, man.

1363
01:46:30,008 --> 01:46:31,342
Drop it now.

1364
01:46:37,099 --> 01:46:39,225
Too high!

1365
01:46:39,518 --> 01:46:43,354
Anticipation, 500 feet!
You've got to take it lower.

1366
01:46:47,734 --> 01:46:50,403
FIREMAN: Can't take
much more of this!

1367
01:46:55,993 --> 01:46:58,911
You've got one more load.
You can do it, Dorinda.

1368
01:47:00,581 --> 01:47:02,456
Drop into the pocket.

1369
01:47:06,920 --> 01:47:08,087
Hold it!

1370
01:47:08,255 --> 01:47:09,338
It's too hot!

1371
01:47:09,423 --> 01:47:11,591
I know, baby, but
you've got to get lower.

1372
01:47:21,602 --> 01:47:23,519
(PANTING)

1373
01:47:28,692 --> 01:47:30,693
PETE: Throttle.
More throttle. (GRUNTS)

1374
01:47:32,946 --> 01:47:34,113
Ride it.

1375
01:47:34,239 --> 01:47:35,364
It's too hot!

1376
01:47:36,617 --> 01:47:38,159
PETE: That's it!
(SCREAMS)

1377
01:48:02,559 --> 01:48:03,643
Now!

1378
01:48:09,149 --> 01:48:10,983
Pull out! Pull out!

1379
01:48:11,902 --> 01:48:13,069
(SCREAMS)

1380
01:48:13,570 --> 01:48:15,112
FIREMAN: Go for the wet spots!

1381
01:48:15,197 --> 01:48:16,989
Go for the wet spots!

1382
01:48:17,991 --> 01:48:19,575
Pull out!

1383
01:48:19,868 --> 01:48:21,202
Twist out!

1384
01:48:21,453 --> 01:48:23,871
That's it. Twisting out!

1385
01:48:25,332 --> 01:48:26,666
That's it.

1386
01:48:31,338 --> 01:48:32,672
(GASPING)

1387
01:48:32,756 --> 01:48:35,591
Get up. That's it.
You're going up.

1388
01:48:49,773 --> 01:48:51,274
(FIREMEN REJOICING)

1389
01:48:51,358 --> 01:48:53,025
FIREMAN: Head downriver!

1390
01:48:56,571 --> 01:48:59,031
This is Tanker 59
to Tanker Base.

1391
01:48:59,199 --> 01:49:00,533
I am fine.

1392
01:49:00,867 --> 01:49:03,035
The jumpers are
in the clear.

1393
01:49:45,203 --> 01:49:47,413
Now I can tell
you everything.

1394
01:49:52,085 --> 01:49:54,712
You'll have a
wonderful life, Dorinda.

1395
01:49:55,797 --> 01:49:59,842
You won't have
any more bad dreams. You'll go to bed happy

1396
01:50:01,595 --> 01:50:03,054
and wake up laughing.

1397
01:50:03,138 --> 01:50:05,890
You'll be with people.
You'll have fun.

1398
01:50:07,434 --> 01:50:09,435
You'll have everything,

1399
01:50:11,146 --> 01:50:12,813
including love.

1400
01:50:17,361 --> 01:50:21,614
I could never tell you
how I felt the way I'm telling you now.

1401
01:50:23,784 --> 01:50:27,370
I'm only a thought,
which you just think is your own.

1402
01:50:30,957 --> 01:50:32,291
But now,

1403
01:50:35,128 --> 01:50:38,047
I can say what I've
always wanted to say.

1404
01:50:42,135 --> 01:50:43,886
I love you, Dorinda.

1405
01:50:46,640 --> 01:50:48,015
(SIGHS)

1406
01:50:48,809 --> 01:50:50,184
I love you.

1407
01:50:52,312 --> 01:50:54,438
I should have told you
that a long time ago,

1408
01:50:56,274 --> 01:50:58,067
without any jokes.

1409
01:50:59,152 --> 01:51:01,445
I should have
said the words

1410
01:51:02,447 --> 01:51:04,657
because I know now that

1411
01:51:05,659 --> 01:51:09,745
the love we hold back
is the only pain that follows us here.

1412
01:51:12,749 --> 01:51:15,000
And the memory
of that love

1413
01:51:15,669 --> 01:51:18,921
shouldn't make you unhappy
for the rest of your life.

1414
01:51:23,427 --> 01:51:26,846
I hope you can hear me
because I know this is true,

1415
01:51:29,433 --> 01:51:33,894
from
the bottom of my heart, how good your life is.

1416
01:51:36,022 --> 01:51:37,773
How good it will be.

1417
01:51:42,112 --> 01:51:43,696
Can you hear me?

1418
01:51:47,284 --> 01:51:50,035
Brush your hair
from your face if you can hear me.

1419
01:51:50,120 --> 01:51:52,621
Brush your hair
away from your face one more time,

1420
01:51:52,706 --> 01:51:56,709
so I can see your eyes
and say "goodbye."

1421
01:52:08,555 --> 01:52:10,055
(ENGINE DYING)

1422
01:52:13,435 --> 01:52:15,227
I'm losing pressure.

1423
01:52:18,732 --> 01:52:20,608
Don't worry.
Try to make it to the water.

1424
01:52:23,111 --> 01:52:25,446
You can make it.
You can do it.

1425
01:52:26,198 --> 01:52:27,865
The water is easy.

1426
01:53:09,616 --> 01:53:11,075
(SPLASHES LOUDLY)

1427
01:53:33,056 --> 01:53:34,598
PETE: Dorinda.

1428
01:53:35,308 --> 01:53:36,642
Dorinda.

1429
01:53:38,562 --> 01:53:40,312
I'm right over here.

1430
01:53:43,984 --> 01:53:45,317
Look at me.

1431
01:54:08,258 --> 01:54:09,967
(YELPS)

1432
01:54:14,764 --> 01:54:16,015
Pete!

1433
01:54:50,967 --> 01:54:52,968
There is the rest
of your life.

1434
01:54:53,053 --> 01:54:56,055
I want you to go to them.
I'm releasing you.

1435
01:54:58,516 --> 01:55:00,684
I'm moving out
of your heart.

1436
01:55:03,396 --> 01:55:04,563
Go on.

1437
01:55:07,400 --> 01:55:08,567
Go on.

1438
01:55:50,318 --> 01:55:51,860
That's my girl.

1439
01:55:55,949 --> 01:55:57,616
And that's my boy.

1440
01:56:25,729 --> 01:56:27,646
(ROMANTIC SONG PLAYING)

